  "doi": "10.1016/j.jbc.2023.104930",
  "title": "Complimentary electrostatics dominate T-cell receptor binding to a psoriasis-associated peptide antigen presented by human leukocyte antigen C\u221706:02.",
  "journal": "The Journal of biological chemistry",
  "year": 2023,
  "authors": "Anand S, Littler DR, Mobbs JI, Braun A, Baker DG, Tennant L, Purcell AW, Vivian JP, Rossjohn J."
 },
 "executive_summary": "A crystal structure of the psoriatic T-cell receptor clone V\u03b13S1/V\u03b213S1 bound to HLA-C\u221706:02 presenting the melanocyte autoantigen peptide VRSRRCLRL (derived from ADAMTSL5) reveals that complementary electrostatics drive recognition, with negatively charged TCR residues forming an extensive charge network with arginine-rich positions in both the peptide and the HLA \u03b11 helix. This charged interaction interface maps to the polymorphic C1/C2 region of HLA-C\u221706:02, the allele conferring highest genetic risk for psoriasis, and suggests that this HLA variant is particularly suited to present arginine-rich epitopes to acidic TCRs. The findings provide molecular insight into how autoreactive T cells target melanocyte antigens in psoriasis and expand understanding of TCR-HLA-C engagement mechanisms more broadly.",
